Available Tools: select_records | select_with_filter | select_with_join | count_records
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "table": "string", "columns": ["string"], "where": "string", "limit": number }
Response Schema: { "rows": [{}], "count": number, "query_ms": number }
---
Question: Retrieve customer names and subscription start dates for the first 8 active members.
Call: { "func_call": "select_with_join", "table": "customers", "columns": ["customers.full_name", "subscriptions.start_date"], "where": "customers.id = subscriptions.customer_id AND subscriptions.status = 'active'", "limit": 8 }
Response: { "rows": [{"full_name": "Laura Chen", "start_date": "2024-01-10"}, {"full_name": "Marcus Thorne", "start_date": "2024-01-12"}, {"full_name": "Nina Patel", "start_date": "2024-01-15"}, {"full_name": "Oscar Ruiz", "start_date": "2024-01-18"}, {"full_name": "Priya Singh", "start_date": "2024-01-20"}, {"full_name": "Quincy Adams", "start_date": "2024-01-22"}, {"full_name": "Rachel Green", "start_date": "2024-01-25"}, {"full_name": "Sam Wilson", "start_date": "2024-01-28"}], "count": 8, "query_ms": 14 }
